.TH "atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_timing" 9 "atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_timing" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_timing \- set the SMC CS conf Txx parameter to a specific value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" atmel_smc_cs_conf_set_timing
.BI "(struct atmel_smc_cs_conf *conf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int shift "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ncycles "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "conf" 12
SMC CS conf descriptor
.IP "shift" 12
the position of the Txx field in the TIMINGS register
.IP "ncycles" 12
value (expressed in MCK clk cycles) to assign to this Txx
parameter
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function encodes the \fIncycles\fP value as described in the datasheet
(section "SMC Timings Register"), and then stores the result in the
\fIconf->timings\fP field at \fIshift\fP position.

Returns -EINVAL if shift is invalid, -ERANGE if ncycles does not fit in
the field, and 0 otherwise.
